<h2><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-38791" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/sliding-windows-tinting.png" alt="" width="680" height="400" /></h2>
<h2>Window Tinting</h2>
Sliding windows traditionally use clear glass in their windows; but there are endless tints, types, and thicknesses available. Arguably, the most popular coating available is LowE. This is a type of tint which helps to minimize harmful UV rays from penetrating a space. By using a LowE glass, you are protecting your furnishings and window treatments from fading. This type of glass also helps maintain a comfortable temperature within the room. Impact glazings are available to meet HVHZ requirements.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-38792" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/sliding-windows.png" alt="" width="680" height="400" /></h2>
<h2>Glazing</h2>
Nearly any glazing selection available on the maker today can be used with Solar InnovationsÂ®â€™s sliding glass windows. This versatility allows for glass or polycarbonate, monolithic, or insulated options to be integrated into our system. If you are trying to achieve a modern appearance with your windows, polycarbonate is one of the easiest ways to meet your goal. There are several different colors of polycarbonate available, including: blue, green, clear, opal, and bronze. Regular glass comes in a variety of thicknesses, as does polycarbonate. 8mm polycarbonate is comparable to single pane glass, 25mm polycarbonate is comparable to insulated glass, and 60mm polycarbonate iscomparable to triple pane glass.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_single_image image="38794" img_size="full"][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2>Gridwork</h2>
By adding grid work, the windows will have a classic, traditional feel. Mullions can be added to the windows to create a modern clean line look. More than one glazing can be placed in between the mullion sections to create an artistic appearance. Several handle options available in numerous finishes are available.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
